First Read: 10-Feb-26
HB410 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 Relating to Limestone County; to amend Section
4 45-42-230, Code of Alabama 1975; and to further provide for
5 the compensation of the sheriff.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
7 Section 1. Section 45-42-230, Code of Alabama 1975, is
8 amended to read as follows:
9 "§45-42-230
10 (a) Beginning with the next term of office, the Sheriff
11 of Limestone County shall receive an annual salary that is 85
12 percent of the annual salary of the highest paid Thirty-ninth
13 Judicial Circuit Court Judge.
14 (b) Beginning January 18, 2027, the Sheriff of
15 Limestone County shall receive a base annual salary of one
16 hundred forty-nine thousand dollars ($149,000) per annum. This
17 salary shall be in lieu of the salary provided in subsection
18 (a) which shall be void.
19 (c) The sheriff shall continue to receive the same
20 cost-of-living increases and other uniform increases as
21 granted to all county employees by the county commission.
22 (b)(d) The sheriff shall not personally financially
23 benefit from the food account used for the feeding of county
24 and state prisoners."
25 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
26 1, 2026.
